Create a sequence diagram for a loan origination process with the following specifications:
Participants:

Applicant (actor)
Loan Origination System (LOS)
Integration & Operations Layer "Converge BankingSuite" containing:

Loan-Service
Equifax-Adapter
Cotality-Adapter
Docmosis-Adapter
DataStore (database)


External systems:

Equifax API
Cotality API
Document Service API
Core Banking System



Process Flow:

Credit Analysis Phase:

LOS requests applicant credit score from Equifax-Adapter
Equifax-Adapter calls Equifax API (POST endpoint for credit reports with JWT authorization)
Return credit report back through the chain


Collateral Valuation Phase:

LOS requests property valuation from Cotality-Adapter
Cotality-Adapter gets property ID from Cotality API
Retrieves AVM valuation data using the property ID
Returns valuation report to LOS


Offer Generation Phase:

Decision branch:

If Approved: Generate offer letter via Docmosis-Adapter â†’ Document Service API, send contract to applicant
If Declined: Generate decline letter via same path, send decline notification to applicant




Account Creation Phase:

Applicant signs contract
LOS triggers loan booking via Loan-Service
Loan-Service creates loan in Core Banking System
Parallel processes:

Confirm loan creation to LOS
Generate loan documents via Docmosis-Adapter
Notify applicant of loan creation





Styling Requirements:

Group I&O Layer components in a light blue box
Center-align box labels
Include appropriate padding
Show activation bars for Document Service API calls
Use alt/else for approval decision
Use par (parallel) for final notifications